<title>USA: Microsoft eyes CBS - New York Post.</title>
<headline>Microsoft eyes CBS - New York Post.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-07-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Microsoft Corp is reviewing the finances of Westinghouse Electric Corp unit CBS and is considering making a bid to buy the network, the New York Post reported Tuesday.</p>
<p>The newspaper, quoting sources close to the situation, said four Microsoft executives were reviewing CBS finances.</p>
<p>Neither Microsoft nor CBS was immediately available for comment, but the Post quoted sources close to CBS as saying the company was not for sale.</p>
<p>The newspaper reported that Seagram Co Ltd &quot;is also said to be looking at CBS.&quot; Seagram owns Universal Studios.</p>
<p>The Microsoft and Seagram interest in CBS was said to be preliminary and it was not clear if offers would be made, the Post said.</p>
<p>Microsoft, Seagram and Westinghouse were quoted as declining comment.</p>
<p>((--New York Newsdesk 212-859-1730))</p>
